    "path": "/multithreading/concurrency",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"book\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#book\" aria-label=\"book permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Book</h2>\n<p>Brian Goetz, Tim Peierls, Joshua Bloch, Joseph Bowbeer, David Holmes, Doug Lea. <strong>Java Concurrency in Practice</strong>, 2006, Addison-Wesley Professional, ISBN 0321349601.</p>\n<p>Read it at <a href=\"https://ubz-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/permalink/f/pok0fm/39UBZ_ALMA_DS51259889720001241\">O'Reilly</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ubz-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/permalink/f/pok0fm/39UBZ_ALMA_DS51259889720001241\"><img src=\"https://learning.oreilly.com/covers/urn:orm:book:0321349601/400w/\" class=\"gatsby-img-attributes\" style=\"width: 300px;\" alt=\"\" title=\"\"/></a></p>\n<h2 id=\"concurrency\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concurrency\" aria-label=\"concurrency permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concurrency</h2>\n<p>We often need to run several programs at the same time:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>streaming a video on Chrome</li>\n<li>coding on IntelliJ</li>\n<li>video conferencing on Teams</li>\n<li>synching your files on the cloud with Dropbox</li>\n<li>reading a pdf on Acrobat</li>\n<li>and many more!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Have you ever wondered how that works?</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-do-you-make-pasta\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-do-you-make-pasta\" aria-label=\"how do you make pasta permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How do you make pasta?</h2>\n<p>Sequentially?</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 731px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7411084035d9828003d54c13f75db8b0/6e9ba/pasta-sequential.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 8.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"pasta-sequential\"\n        title=\"pasta-sequential\"\n        src=\"/static/7411084035d9828003d54c13f75db8b0/6e9ba/pasta-sequential.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7411084035d9828003d54c13f75db8b0/772e8/pasta-sequential.png 200w,\n/static/7411084035d9828003d54c13f75db8b0/e17e5/pasta-sequential.png 400w,\n/static/7411084035d9828003d54c13f75db8b0/6e9ba/pasta-sequential.png 731w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 731px) 100vw, 731px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Concurrently?</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 621px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/829392bacb3e9d289a714ec2a5c2d9a8/3075e/pasta-concurrent.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 27.500000000000004%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"pasta-concurrent\"\n        title=\"pasta-concurrent\"\n        src=\"/static/829392bacb3e9d289a714ec2a5c2d9a8/3075e/pasta-concurrent.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/829392bacb3e9d289a714ec2a5c2d9a8/772e8/pasta-concurrent.png 200w,\n/static/829392bacb3e9d289a714ec2a5c2d9a8/e17e5/pasta-concurrent.png 400w,\n/static/829392bacb3e9d289a714ec2a5c2d9a8/3075e/pasta-concurrent.png 621w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 621px) 100vw, 621px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"scheduling-sequential-vs-concurrent\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#scheduling-sequential-vs-concurrent\" aria-label=\"scheduling sequential vs concurrent permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Scheduling: Sequential vs Concurrent</h2>\n<p><strong>Sequential scheduling</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dependent computations</strong> that must be executed in an <strong>specific order</strong> to produce correct results</li>\n<li>Up to now, all the programs we developed in this course worked in a sequential way</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Concurrent scheduling</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Independent computations</strong> that can be executed in an <strong>arbitrary order</strong> with the same outcome</li>\n<li>A computation can advance without waiting for all other computations to complete</li>\n<li>A computation can be constrained by depending on interaction between computations</li>\n<li><em>Minimizing dependencies while preserving correctness is the central problem</em>.</li>\n<li>Concurrent programming means factoring a program into independent modules or units of concurrency.</li>\n<li>Units of concurrency:\n<ul>\n<li>tasks,</li>\n<li>processes,</li>\n<li>threads,</li>\n<li>actors...</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Definitions from <a href=\"https://slikts.github.io/concurrency-glossary\">https://slikts.github.io/concurrency-glossary</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"execution-serial-vs-parallel\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#execution-serial-vs-parallel\" aria-label=\"execution serial vs parallel permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Execution: Serial vs Parallel</h2>\n<p><strong>Serial execution</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Executing computations one-at-a-time</li>\n<li>Concurrent processes can be executed on one core:\n<ul>\n<li>Enables <em>pseudo parallelism</em></li>\n<li>by interleaving the execution steps of each process via time-sharing slices</li>\n<li><strong>only one process runs at a time</strong>, and if it does not complete during its time slice, it is <strong>paused</strong>, another process <strong>begins or resumes</strong>, and then later the original process is resumed.</li>\n<li>multiple processes are part-way through execution at a single instant, but only one process is being executed at that instant</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Parallel execution</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Executing multiple computations at the same physical instant</li>\n<li>Concurrent processes can be executed in multiple cores:\n<ul>\n<li>Enables <em>true parallelism</em></li>\n<li>on separate processors of a multi-processor machine, with the goal of speeding up computations</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Definitions from <a href=\"https://slikts.github.io/concurrency-glossary\">https://slikts.github.io/concurrency-glossary</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"concurrency-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concurrency-1\" aria-label=\"concurrency 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concurrency</h2>\n<p><strong>Pseudo parallelism</strong>: concurrent scheduling and serial execution:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/1c7bc/interleaving-execution.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"interleaving execution\"\n        title=\"interleaving execution\"\n        src=\"/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/4b190/interleaving-execution.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/e07e9/interleaving-execution.jpg 200w,\n/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/066f9/interleaving-execution.jpg 400w,\n/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/4b190/interleaving-execution.jpg 800w,\n/static/d02379af5babc19e15c49a562002712e/1c7bc/interleaving-execution.jpg 1023w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>True parallelism</strong>: concurrent scheduling and parallel execution:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/1c7bc/parallel-execution.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"parallel execution\"\n        title=\"parallel execution\"\n        src=\"/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/4b190/parallel-execution.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/e07e9/parallel-execution.jpg 200w,\n/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/066f9/parallel-execution.jpg 400w,\n/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/4b190/parallel-execution.jpg 800w,\n/static/fd63dbcbf2c9c43b215f13656a23e6e5/1c7bc/parallel-execution.jpg 1023w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"concurrency-2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concurrency-2\" aria-label=\"concurrency 2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concurrency</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Task scheduling: concurrent vs sequential</li>\n<li>Task execution: parallel vs serial</li>\n<li>Example: cooking pasta, 2 tasks scheduled concurrently\n<ul>\n<li>boiling pasta</li>\n<li>preparing sauce </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Example: consider tasks T1 and T2\n<ul>\n<li>T1 must be executed before T2 (sequential and serial)</li>\n<li>T1 can be executed before T2 or vice versa (concurrent and serial)</li>\n<li>T1 and T2 are executed simultaneously (concurrent and parallel)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"concurrency-level\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#concurrency-level\" aria-label=\"concurrency level permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Concurrency level</h2>\n<p>Concurrency can take place on many levels:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>low-level hardware on a single chip</li>\n<li><strong>operating system</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>process</li>\n<li>thread</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>worldwide networks</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"shared-resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#shared-resources\" aria-label=\"shared resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Shared resources</h2>\n<p>The main challenge in concurrent programming is concurrency control:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>ensuring correct <strong>communication between concurrent executions</strong></li>\n<li>coordinating access to <strong>resources shared</strong> among concurrent executions</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here is an example of a bug caused by an improper handling of a shared resource</p>\n<ul>\n<li>We have two threads.</li>\n<li>Each thread executes one line, pauses, and the other thread resumes.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">boolean</span> <span class=\"token function\">withdraw</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> withdrawal<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>balance <span class=\"token operator\">>=</span> withdrawal<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    balance <span class=\"token operator\">-=</span> withdrawal<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> \n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Thread 1:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"output\"><pre class=\"language-output\"><code class=\"language-output\">balance = 500\nstep 1: withdraw(300)\nstep 3: true (line 2)\nstep 5: balance = 200 (line 3)</code></pre></div>\n<p>Thread 2:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"output\"><pre class=\"language-output\"><code class=\"language-output\">balance = 500\nstep 2: withdraw(350)\nstep 4: true (line 2)\nstep 6: balance = -150 (line 3)</code></pre></div>\n<p>Thread 2 actually bypassed the if statement that prevent overdrafting the account. To prevent the occurrence of such an issue, we need to coordinate the execution of these threads!</p>","frontmatter":{"slug":"/multithreading/concurrency","title":"Concurrency","course":"Programming Project 2021/22","previous":"/serialization/serializable","next":"/multithreading/processes-threads","chapter":18,"section":1,"module":"Multithreading","banner":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/multithreading/concurrency"}},
    "staticQueryHashes": ["800307450"]}